<subSubSection id="C5BCF8D23208FFF05CCF0249FF03FD68" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8D19AB593208FFF05CCF0249FF03FD68" blockId="6.[166,1225,559,874]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. From Fennoscandia southwards to Iberian Peninsula and the Mediterranean region (including Crete); from Britain eastwards through Central and Southern Europe to the Balkans and 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC93208FFF05EAF0216FCEFFD4B" box="[699,795,623,649]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Turkey</collectingCountry>
; Northern Africa; 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC93208FFF0581F0209FBB5FD48" box="[1035,1089,624,650]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E937D6A83208FFF058470216FF1EFD68" author="Gilasian, E." pageId="6" pageNumber="407" pagination="75 - 76" refId="ref6509" refString="Gilasian, E. New record of one genus and six species of Syrphidae (Diptera) from Iran // J. Entomological Society of Iran. - 2005. - 25, N 1. - P. 75 - 76." type="book chapter" year="2005">Gilasian, 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C5BCF8D23208FFF05CCF02C9FC5AFCA8" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8D19AB593208FFF05CCF02C9FC5AFCA8" blockId="6.[166,1225,559,874]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">
D i a g n o s t i c c h a r a c t e r s. Eye with short white hairs in dorsal half; face without distinct hairs (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC3208FFF05D5802B6FE73FD2B" box="[332,391,719,745]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[170,203,1669,1691]" captionTargetBox="[173,1228,862,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-318@5.[169,1228,862,1644]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Cheilosia rufipes (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — frontal view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. aruralis, female (d–f): d — dorsal view, e — frontal view of head, f — lateral view; Cheilosia scutellata male (g–i): g — lateral view, h — frontal view of head, i — genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449155/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B3208FFF05D8702A9FE6BFD2B" box="[403,415,720,745]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">e</emphasis>
) (microtrichia not taken into account); parafacial without pruinosity, lustrous; mesoscutum with short hairs; femora entirely yellow in female; All tibiae with more or less wide black ring; at least first and second segments of mid tarsus or bases of tibiae yellow (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC3208FFF05D590356FE7EFC8B" box="[333,394,815,841]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[170,203,1669,1691]" captionTargetBox="[173,1228,862,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-318@5.[169,1228,862,1644]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Cheilosia rufipes (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — frontal view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. aruralis, female (d–f): d — dorsal view, e — frontal view of head, f — lateral view; Cheilosia scutellata male (g–i): g — lateral view, h — frontal view of head, i — genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449155/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B3208FFF05D8D0356FE55FC8B" box="[409,417,815,841]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">f</emphasis>
); posterior margin of scutellum with hairs, without strong black or yellow bristles; abdomen with recumbent hairs medially (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC3208FFF05F520336FC75FCAB" box="[838,897,847,873]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[170,203,1669,1691]" captionTargetBox="[173,1228,862,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-318@5.[169,1228,862,1644]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Cheilosia rufipes (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — frontal view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. aruralis, female (d–f): d — dorsal view, e — frontal view of head, f — lateral view; Cheilosia scutellata male (g–i): g — lateral view, h — frontal view of head, i — genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449155/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B3208FFF05F9A0336FC69FCAB" box="[910,925,847,873]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">d</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
